<!-- ABSTRACT -->
<h1 class="chapter-title">ABSTRACT</h1>
<p style="line-height: 2;">SHREE Collective is a premium, full-stack luxury Indian couture e-commerce platform designed to digitize the high-fashion ethnic wear market. The platform bridges traditional craftsmanship—such as zardozi embroidery, gota patti work, and heritage Banarasi silks—with a cutting-edge, modern web experience. Built using a decoupled architecture, it leverages React 19 and Vite for a highly responsive frontend, Node.js and Express for a robust RESTful API, and MongoDB for flexible NoSQL data storage. The application features a comprehensive product catalog, a secure JWT-based authentication system supporting both email and Google OAuth via Firebase, an end-to-end cart and checkout flow, and an administrative dashboard for catalog and order management. Performance optimizations, including IntersectionObserver-based lazy loading and CSS skeleton loaders, ensure a seamless, high-performance user experience. The project serves as a comprehensive demonstration of modern full-stack web development, addressing the unique digital requirements of the luxury fashion industry.</p>

