<!-- APPENDIX -->
<h1 class="chapter-title">APPENDIX</h1>
<h2>User Manual</h2>
<p><strong>Step 1: Application Setup</strong><br>
1. Clone the repository from GitHub.<br>
2. Navigate to the project directory and run <code>npm install</code> in both the root and <code>server/</code> directories.<br>
3. Configure the <code>.env</code> file in the <code>server/</code> directory with MongoDB URI, JWT Secret, and Cloudinary credentials.</p>

<p><strong>Step 2: Database Seeding</strong><br>
Run <code>npm run seed</code> in the <code>server/</code> directory to populate the initial product catalog into MongoDB.</p>

<p><strong>Step 3: Running the Application</strong><br>
1. Start the backend server by running <code>npm start</code> in the <code>server/</code> directory.<br>
2. Start the frontend development server by running <code>npm run dev</code> in the root directory.<br>
3. Access the application at <code>http://localhost:5173</code> in your web browser.</p>

<h2>Achievements</h2>
<p>The project successfully integrated complete CI/CD pipelines, achieved over 90+ Lighthouse performance scores across all metrics, and implemented a flawless zero-layout-shift experience utilizing advanced CSS skeleton loading techniques.</p>

